section.p:
All the properties defined in an trinidad-config.xml
file can be retrieved programatically with the
org.apache.myfaces.trinidad.context.RequestContext class.
One instance of this class exists per request, and it can
be retrieved using the static getCurrentInstance()
method (just like a FacesContext).  Despite the name,
RequestContext does not actually extend
FacesContext.

         RequestContext context = RequestContext.getCurrentInstance();

         // Get the time zone
         TimeZone zone = context.getTimeZone();

         // Are we in a right-to-left language?
         if (context.isRightToLeft())
         {
           ...
         }


In addition to the configuration properties described above, the
RequestContext object also exposes several properties
of type java.util.Map that help users write EL
expressions (see the next section for information on this 
use). For more information, see the Javadoc for this class.
